   GLOBAL FIX: Adopt safer string handling practices such as using size-safe
   string manipulation functions, or wrap C-style strings in a structure that
   always manages its own length and allocation size automatically, ensuring
   space for a terminator. Alternatively, using higher-level string handling
   libraries or languages with built-in string safety can eliminate buffer
   overflows by managing these details internally.
